
---

# 🚫 `.gitignore`

This `.gitignore` is tailored **exactly** for your project.

```gitignore
# ======================
# Python
# ======================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
*.pyd

# ======================
# Virtual Environments
# ======================
.StockVenv/
venv/
env/

# ======================
# Jupyter
# ======================
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ======================
# VS Code
# ======================
.vscode/

# ======================
# OS files
# ======================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ======================
# Data & Outputs (large / reproducible)
# ======================
data/*.csv
outputs/*.html
outputs/
notebooks/*.ipynb
models/*.pkl
models_improved/*.pkl
models_improved/*.joblib
models_improved/*.pt
models_improved/*.h5
models_clf/
models/
*.csv
*.pkl

# ======================
# Models (optional: keep or ignore)
# Uncomment if you DON'T want models on GitHub
# models/*.pkl

# ======================
# Logs
# ======================
*.log

# ======================
# Streamlit cache
# ======================
.streamlit/

# ======================
# Secrets (future broker keys)
# ======================
.env
.env.*
